olive oil
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 cucumber
1 tomato
½ lemon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet beef strips
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend

Boil a kettle of water. Place couscous and chicken-style stock powder in a
medium bowl. Add the boiling water and stir to combine. Immediately cover
with a plate and set aside for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork, then add a drizzle
of olive oil.

While the couscous is cooking, roughly chop the cucumber and tomato. Slice
the lemon into wedges. In a second medium bowl, combine a squeeze of
lemon juice with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the cucumber, tomato and baby
spinach leaves. Toss to coat and season to taste.

Heat a large frying pan over a high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the
beef strips, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 2-3 minutes. Add
the Louisiana spice blend with a dash of water and toss until the beef is well
coated, 1 minute.
TIP: Cook the beef in batches if your pan is getting crowded.

In a small bowl, combine the sour cream with a squeeze of lemon juice and
season to taste. Divide the couscous between bowls. Top with the Louisiana
beef and cucumber salad. Spoon over the lemon sour cream. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges.